WhatsApp Integration & OTP Login Implementation Plan
Yeh document aapke Doctor Appointment System me WhatsApp Cloud API integrate karne, Patient OTP login implement karne, aur automated notifications send karne ka ek complete, step-by-step architectural plan hai.

1. Meta (Facebook) Developer Account Setup
WhatsApp Cloud API use karne ke liye hume sabse pehle Meta par setup karna hoga:

Developer Account: developers.facebook.com par ja kar login/signup karein.
Create App: "My Apps" > "Create App" > "Other" > "Business" select karein.
Add WhatsApp Product: App dashboard me "WhatsApp" product add karein aur "API Setup" par jayein.
Get Credentials: Yahan se aapko Temporary Access Token, Phone Number ID, aur WhatsApp Business Account ID milega (Production ke liye aapko inka Permanent Access Token generate karna hoga).
Create Message Templates: WhatsApp API me direct custom messages bhejmana allow nahi hota (24-hour window ke baahar). Humein Meta dashboard me templates approve karwane honge:
OTP Template: Aapka login OTP hai: {{1}}. Yeh 5 minute tak valid hai.
Booking Template: Hello {{1}}, aapki appointment Dr. {{2}} ke saath {{3}} ko confirm ho gayi hai.
Prescription Template: Hello {{1}}, aapka recent visit ka prescription generate ho gaya hai. Aap ise yahan check kar sakte hain: {{2}}
2. Django auth_user Password/Username Solution
Aapka sawal tha ki Django ka default User model password aur username mandatory maangta hai, jabki humein OTP se login karwana hai. Iska best aur standard solution yeh hai:

Solution: Custom Authentication Backend
Hum Django ke default login system ko over-ride karenge. User backend me hi banega, lekin password mangne ki zaroorat nahi padegi.

Username: Jab koi naya patient number daalega, hum uska phone number hi as a username store kar lenge (ya fir ek auto-generated random ID patient_919876543210).
Password: Hum Django ka ek built-in function use karenge: user.set_unusable_password(). Isse backend me ek dummy hash set ho jata hai jisse koi normal password daal kar login nahi kar sakta.
Custom Auth Backend (accounts/backends.py): Ek custom backend class likhenge WhatsAppOTPBackend. Jab user correct OTP daalega, hum manually is backend ke through Django ko batayenge ki "Ye OTP sahi hai, is user ko bina password check kiye authenticate kar do".
